                  <interp inst="t18290409-267-crimeloc1504" type="placeName" value="New Brentford"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18290409-267-crimeloc1504" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18290409-267-off1501 t18290409-267-crimeloc1504"></join>. We lost this scarf and pair of breeches, on the 7th of April, from inside the shop door; I had seen the prisoner in the town.</p>
               <p>
                  <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="182904090121"></xptr>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-267-person2455">
                  JOHN 
                  COPE FOLKARD
               <interp inst="t18290409-267-person2455" type="surname" value="COPE FOLKARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-267-person2455" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-267-person2455" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a pawnbroker, and live at Old Brentford. About half-past eight o'clock on this evening this pair of breeches was brought to me by the prisoner; he wanted five shillings on them - I had received information; I said,</p>
               <p>"Very well." and told my young man to make out the duplicate; I went round to try to shut the door, but he saw my intention, and ran off; I followed; he fell down, got up, and ran again.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18290409-267-person2456">
                  JOSEPH 
                  DICKENSON
               <interp inst="t18290409-267-person2456" type="surname" value="DICKENSON"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-267-person2456" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18290409-267-person2456" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I was coming down the town, and heard the cry of Stop thief! I saw the prisoner running; I pursued, and caught him; as I was taking him to the cage, I saw him stoop; I looked, and found this scarf.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I was at Brentford, and met a man, who asked me where there was a pawnbroker's; I went to show him; he asked me to take these things in - he said he would give me sixpence, and the ticket - he told me to ask five shillings, and if they would lend it, I was to go and tell him; I went to tell him, and the gentleman came to take me.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t18290409-267-verdict1505" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18290409-267-verdict1505" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>. Aged. 20.</p>
